The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Krishna to visit Japan
                                                                                                               Krishna to visit Japan
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT       
	New Delhi, June 29: External affairs minister S.M. Krishna will travel to Tokyo this week to attend the third annual strategic dialogue between India and Japan.        
	During the July 3-4 visit, Krishna will call on Japanese Prime Minister Taro Aso and inaugurate the Indian embassys new building in Tokyo, the external affairs ministry said in a release today.        
	Krishna will also hold talks with his Japanese counterpart, Hirofumi Nakasone, on a wide range of bilateral and global issues, including steps to deepen bilateral economic ties and ways to cope with the global financial crisis.        
	Climate change will be also be an important theme in the discussions, taking place days before the G8 summit in Italy on July 9 and 10. Prime Minister Manmohan Singh is scheduled to attend the summit.        
	At the embassy inauguration, Krishna will meet members of the Indian community, the external affairs ministry said in a release today.                                                                                                                                                                           
